---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — vibs.io"
  description="How vibs.io handles your data: your plans live in your URL and your browser, not on our servers."
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main id="main" class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Effective date: July 11, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">The short version</h2>
        <p>
          vibs.io is built so your planning data does not need to touch our servers. Your workspace —
          project details, backlog items, velocity history, and generated blueprints — is compressed
          into the URL in your address bar and mirrored to your browser's local storage. If you never
          sign in, your data never leaves your device unless you choose to share a link.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Data stored in your browser</h2>
        <p>
          We use your browser's local storage to recover workspaces after a refresh or a closed tab,
          to remember your theme preference, and to keep a local index of your saved workspaces. This
          data stays on your device. Clearing your browser storage removes it permanently.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Shareable links</h2>
        <p>
          When you copy a vibs.io URL, the full workspace state travels inside that link. Anyone you
          share the link with can see the plan it contains. Treat workspace links like documents:
          share them only with people who should read them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">If you sign in</h2>
        <p>
          Sign-in is optional and only required for AI-powered features. Authentication is handled by
          Supabase using Google OAuth. When you sign in, we receive your name, email address, and
          profile picture from Google, and we store an authentication session in your browser. We do
          not receive or store your Google password.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">AI features and the PII filter</h2>
        <p>
          When you use AI generation as a signed-in user, the text you submit is processed by our
          serverless infrastructure to produce your blueprint. Before anything is sent, a filter runs
          locally in your browser and replaces common sensitive patterns — IP addresses, access keys,
          tokens, and email addresses — with generic placeholders. AI inputs are used only to produce
          your requested output; they are not used to train models.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">What we don't do</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your data. We do not run third-party advertising. We do not use invasive
          cross-site tracking.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:silverspectrummedia@gmail.com" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400">silverspectrummedia@gmail.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-sm">
      <a href="/" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400">← Back to the workspace</a>
    </p>
  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-slate-200 py-6 dark:border-slate-800">
    <p class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 text-xs text-slate-400 sm:px-6 dark:text-slate-500">
      vibs.io · <a href="/privacy" class="hover:underline">Privacy</a> · <a href="/terms" class="hover:underline">Terms</a>
    </p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
